The paper deals with computational complexity and approximability of a problem related to planar graphs and their triangulations, which falls under the category of computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of fixed radii disks and the problem of intersecting line segments with these disks suggests a connection to data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The proposed approximation algorithm and its time complexity involve numerical analysis (cs.NA) and simulation and modeling (cs.SI).
